# Invariants & contracts
  @contract  centre is logical; radius is screen px so the dot stays round under non-uniform scale.  @ 189
  @contract  centre is logical; radius is screen px and angles pass through, so arcs need sx==sy.  @ 226
  @contract  x is the strip's horizontal centre, yBottom its bottom edge; size is screen px  @ 249
  @contract  returns false (drawing nothing) when the LICE path is unavailable; callers fall back  @ 250

